    {
      "_id": "019e9e43f24b2561",
      "name": "1 Round of Combat",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 3,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81a2-bf51-f7bf20426293\">This is a span of 12 seconds where each creature in combat takes 1 turn.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8192-bfce-dedf038e738d\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\">DC Tip: Referring to the first round of combat means the FIRST 12 seconds, where each creature will have 1 turn. But if a PC uses an ability that lasts for 1 Round… that effect still lasts 12 seconds (which means each creature will have 1 turn since the use of that ability), and it would last until the start of that creatures next turn.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
