    {
      "_id": "ed009fdf942bddb3",
      "name": "Game Master Initiative Sidebar",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 15,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81a3-8ee9-f9cc20b4bce7\">Here are some bonus Tips for GMs to handle Initiative in some unique situations.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.ed009fdf942bddb3"
    },
    {
      "_id": "4c148e96cde57a4b",
      "name": "Choosing Enemy Initiative Order",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 16,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-811d-9d05-fbae226856e5\">The GM has a number of options when determining how to place enemies within the Initiative order. GMs could choose to place enemies tactically in order to make a Combat Encounter more difficult, create suspense by placing hidden enemies late in Initiative order, or follow the narrative by allowing enemies that have been recently interacted with or targeted by a PC to go directly after them in response.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.4c148e96cde57a4b"
    },
    {
      "_id": "4e4ab7a2e5672b5d",
      "name": "Enemy Groupings",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 17,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81c6-9c15-f568e6db31cf\">The GM may find it simpler to group similar enemies together, rather than spacing them throughout the Initiative Order.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8190-af36-e9871941497e\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\">Example: If there are 4 Goblins with 1 Hobgoblin Boss in a Combat Encounter with 4 PCs. The GM might want to group up the 4 Goblins together in Initiative and then have the Hobgoblin Boss go next. Initiative Order could look like this (if the Enemy Team won Initiative): 4 Goblins, PC #1, PC #2, Hobgoblin Boss, PC #3, PC #4.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.4e4ab7a2e5672b5d"
    },
    {
      "_id": "115b9b51bedcba7a",
      "name": "Unequal Number of Enemies",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 18,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81bf-95a1-eac80d1826dc\">If there is an unequal number of enemies and PCs, the GM may choose to space the Teams out evenly rather than alternating them.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81de-98f1-fa3c46ad9905\"><strong><span>Examples</span></strong></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8132-938c-e5df67b04f3f\"><strong>Evenly Spaced:</strong> PC #1, PC #2, <strong>Enemy #1</strong>, PC #3, PC #4, <strong>Enemy #2</strong></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8164-a0d1-c75f4c68ea08\"><strong>Alternating:</strong> PC #1, <strong>Enemy #1</strong>, PC #2, <strong>Enemy #2</strong>, PC #3, PC #4</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": 1750867587043,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.115b9b51bedcba7a"
    },
    {
      "_id": "e761ca8dc808b296",
      "name": "Multiple Teams",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 19,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8184-b524-cc1dcee29f90\">If there are two or more Enemy Teams, Initiative order will alternate giving a combatant from each Enemy Team and the PC Team a turn. To determine which of the Enemy Teams goes first, the GM can either use a Fate Check or simply choose based on strategy or narrative.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.e761ca8dc808b296"
    },
    {
      "_id": "c4e97a0e31d70d08",
      "name": "Surprise",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 20,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8198-b5e3-dd7c553469f2\">Combat starts as soon as the GM declares “Roll for Initiative.” There are a few things that can happen based on the GMs decision of how the Combat started.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.c4e97a0e31d70d08"
    },
    {
      "_id": "acf1627233b930ab",
      "name": "Pre-Combat Action",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 21,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-818f-8fd6-fa9e17fd1963\">The exact moment a Combat Encounter begins is not always clear cut. A GM may rule that an action performed by a PC triggers a Combat Encounter, in which case the PC may be able to perform that action prior to Initiative. In the case of an already hostile environment, a GM may rule that a PC attempting to perform an action is enough to trigger the Combat Encounter and the action could happen on the PC’s turn if they still want to at that time.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.acf1627233b930ab"
    },
    {
      "_id": "1a0f2951f4907dd6",
      "name": "Ambush",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 22,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8108-bcf5-d4981afffafb\">Not all combatants will be aware of the threat of danger and may find themselves Surprised during the first round of a Combat Encounter. In order to Ambush a Team you need to be able to see the other Team without them being able to see you. If this happens and the GM asks to “Roll for Initiative,'' each creature that was unaware that Combat was starting has the Surprised Condition for the  first Round of Combat.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.1a0f2951f4907dd6"
    },
    {
      "_id": "a9e4e6c5f83084f9",
      "name": "Surprised Condition",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 23,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81b0-9e28-c5ea21019509\">You can’t spend Action Points and are <strong>Exposed</strong> (Attack Checks against you have ADV).</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null,
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.a9e4e6c5f83084f9"
    },
    {
      "name": "Pre-Combat Aggression",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1,
        "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3
      },
      "sort": 4,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81a0-8dd7-c4dbe4fc0d79\">The moment a Combat Encounter begins is not always a matter of strict timing. The GM may determine that a PC’s action (such as drawing steel, loosing an arrow, or invoking a spell) triggers the clash, allowing them to carry out that action before Initiative is rolled. However, if the enemy is already on high alert or poised for battle, the GM may rule that combat begins before the action can be completed, requiring the character to take their aggressive move on their first turn instead.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": "Compendium.dc20rpg.rules.JournalEntry.hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.JournalEntryPage.5e41bbee1cfb718f",
        "coreVersion": "13.344",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": 1744873329460,
        "modifiedTime": 1744873357151,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
        "exportSource": null
      },
      "_id": "AWk0NGWCckwpDRLO",
      "category": null,
      "_key": "!journal.pages!hURAw4P8YtLiqg0i.AWk0NGWCckwpDRLO"
    },
    {
      "name": "Individual Outcomes",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1,
        "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3
      },
      "sort": 8,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p>Use the following Success and Failure Statements to determine the outcome of your Initiative Check:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> You gain a <strong>d6</strong> Inspiration Die, which you can add to 1 Check or Save of your choice that you make during this Combat. The Inspiration Die expires when the Combat ends.</p></li><li><p><strong>Critical Success:</strong> You gain ADV on 1 Check or Save of your choice during the first Round of Combat.</p></li><li><p><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The first Attack made against you during the first Round of Combat has ADV.</p></li></ul>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
